WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.466 --> 00:00:04.466
When you put your face close to the mirror,

00:00:04.466 --> 00:00:08.333
does your skin look like this?

00:00:08.333 --> 00:00:11.866
But if you search online for

00:00:11.866 --> 00:00:15.433
products to shrink pores, do the products that come out look like this?

00:00:15.433 --> 00:00:17.900
And after you use all the products,

00:00:17.900 --> 00:00:22.066
does your skin become like this?

00:00:22.533 --> 00:00:25.900
Today we will talk about how to solve the problem of pores

00:00:33.200 --> 00:00:35.533
. Okay, if you want to solve the problem of pores,

00:00:35.533 --> 00:00:37.633
we must first start by accurately

00:00:37.633 --> 00:00:40.666
determining the type of pores we have.

00:00:40.733 --> 00:00:41.900
So how do we determine this?

00:00:41.900 --> 00:00:43.433
I have summarized 5 dimensions

00:00:43.433 --> 00:00:44.700
to help you determine

00:00:44.700 --> 00:00:47.466
what type of pores you have on your face.

00:00:47.666 --> 00:00:49.633
The first dimension is color.

00:00:49.633 --> 00:00:52.466
Are your pores the same color as your skin

00:00:52.466 --> 00:00:54.066
, or darker than your skin?

00:00:54.066 --> 00:00:55.866
Are they black, brown

00:00:55.866 --> 00:00:57.400
, or red?

00:00:57.400 --> 00:00:59.366
The second is height.

00:00:59.366 --> 00:01:02.533
Are they parallel to the surface of your skin

00:01:02.533 --> 00:01:03.600
, or are they raised

00:01:03.600 --> 00:01:04.900
or sunken?

00:01:04.900 --> 00:01:06.700
The third is height. Is the shape

00:01:06.700 --> 00:01:09.333
of this hole a perfect circle

00:01:09.333 --> 00:01:11.000
or a teardrop?

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:12.800
The fourth is to see

00:01:12.800 --> 00:01:14.000
if it reflects light. Is it matte

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:15.433
or shiny?

00:01:15.433 --> 00:01:18.833
The fifth is to see if something can be squeezed out.

00:01:18.833 --> 00:01:20.866
Is the squeezed out white,

00:01:20.866 --> 00:01:22.900
gray, soft or hard?

00:01:22.900 --> 00:01:25.833
Next, I will

00:01:25.833 --> 00:01:27.866
explain

00:01:27.866 --> 00:01:29.800
the five types of pores

00:01:30.133 --> 00:01:32.633
based on these five dimensions . The first type is oily pores.

00:01:32.633 --> 00:01:35.233
The appearance characteristics of oily pores are as follows:

00:01:35.233 --> 00:01:37.633
its color is generally the same as

00:01:37.633 --> 00:01:39.333
your skin color, parallel

00:01:39.333 --> 00:01:40.433
to the face,

00:01:40.433 --> 00:01:42.000
neither raised nor sunken.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:43.866
The shape is generally a perfect circle. The round

00:01:43.866 --> 00:01:46.400
hole will have obvious oily

00:01:46.400 --> 00:01:49.866
reflections. It can usually be squeezed out by hand to produce

00:01:49.866 --> 00:01:51.300
small white, soft particles.

00:01:51.300 --> 00:01:52.333
Its location is

00:01:52.333 --> 00:01:53.700
generally in the triangle area

00:01:53.700 --> 00:01:56.266
, which is where we usually have oily pores.

00:01:56.266 --> 00:01:57.900
The reason for the formation of this type of pore

00:01:57.900 --> 00:01:59.433
is due to vigorous oil production

00:01:59.433 --> 00:02:01.400
. The pores are enlarged

00:02:01.400 --> 00:02:03.100
and look very large.

00:02:03.100 --> 00:02:04.200
In addition,

00:02:04.200 --> 00:02:07.100
the shiny mirror reflection caused by oil production

00:02:07.100 --> 00:02:09.833
makes the whole skin look dirty and rough.

00:02:09.933 --> 00:02:12.533
The second type is keratinized pores.

00:02:12.533 --> 00:02:13.500
These pores

00:02:13.500 --> 00:02:15.833
are usually slightly higher

00:02:15.833 --> 00:02:18.400
than the skin color and

00:02:18.400 --> 00:02:19.500
slightly raised .

00:02:19.500 --> 00:02:21.933
Generally speaking, they are mainly round holes.

00:02:21.933 --> 00:02:23.533
Some will have oily sheen, while

00:02:23.533 --> 00:02:24.733
others will not be obvious.

00:02:24.733 --> 00:02:27.300
When you squeeze them, they are very difficult to squeeze

00:02:27.300 --> 00:02:28.800
out. However

00:02:28.800 --> 00:02:32.000
, if something is squeezed out, it is usually hard gray particles.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:33.033
The location is

00:02:33.033 --> 00:02:35.066
usually on both sides of the nose and

00:02:35.066 --> 00:02:37.133
half of the cheek.

00:02:37.133 --> 00:02:37.933
Sometimes,

00:02:37.933 --> 00:02:39.100
if it is acne-prone skin,

00:02:39.100 --> 00:02:41.600
it will overlap with the acne area.

00:02:41.600 --> 00:02:43.400
People with keratinized pores

00:02:43.400 --> 00:02:46.400
often have closed comedones

00:02:46.400 --> 00:02:48.700
because both closed comedones and keratinized pores

00:02:48.700 --> 00:02:52.700
are caused by abnormal keratin metabolism. That is to say

00:02:52.700 --> 00:02:55.000
, you have too much old dead skin cells

00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:57.200
that are not discharged from your body in time,

00:02:57.200 --> 00:02:58.466
so they are either blocked

00:02:58.466 --> 00:03:01.400
or arched up near the pores.

00:03:01.400 --> 00:03:02.600
This type of

00:03:02.600 --> 00:03:04.933
pores sometimes

00:03:04.933 --> 00:03:07.633
appear at the same time as the first type, which is oily pores.

00:03:07.833 --> 00:03:10.133
The third type is saccharified pores.

00:03:10.133 --> 00:03:11.666
The color of this type of pores

00:03:11.666 --> 00:03:13.400
is generally darker brown at the edges.

00:03:13.400 --> 00:03:15.266
The

00:03:15.266 --> 00:03:16.933
height

00:03:16.933 --> 00:03:18.633
is parallel to the surface of the skin

00:03:18.633 --> 00:03:20.500
or slightly concave.

00:03:20.500 --> 00:03:22.266
Generally speaking, they are mainly round holes,

00:03:22.266 --> 00:03:23.933
and sometimes they are oval.

00:03:23.933 --> 00:03:25.900
Generally, they are not accompanied by oily sheen

00:03:25.900 --> 00:03:26.866
, have no reflections

00:03:26.933 --> 00:03:28.433
, and can't squeeze out anything.

00:03:28.466 --> 00:03:29.333
This type of pores

00:03:29.333 --> 00:03:31.500
usually appear more

00:03:31.500 --> 00:03:32.800
in the forehead or cheeks

00:03:32.800 --> 00:03:34.700
. Because the outer edge of the pores

00:03:34.700 --> 00:03:36.466
looks like a brown circle , it

00:03:36.466 --> 00:03:37.866
looks like tiny spots

00:03:37.866 --> 00:03:40.066
when you look at it from a distance

00:03:40.066 --> 00:03:43.133
. It can only be seen when you get close to the mirror. When I looked closely, I found

00:03:43.133 --> 00:03:44.466
that there was a hole in the middle.

00:03:44.466 --> 00:03:45.333
It is a pore.

00:03:45.533 --> 00:03:46.833
This is actually because

00:03:46.833 --> 00:03:49.066
your entire face is undergoing glycation

00:03:49.066 --> 00:03:51.900
, and the pores are just one of them.

00:03:51.900 --> 00:03:54.700
Therefore, when taking care of your skin, you also need to fight sugar on the entire face

00:03:54.700 --> 00:03:56.866
instead of using local products.

00:03:57.266 --> 00:03:59.133
4. Inflammatory pores.

00:03:59.133 --> 00:04:01.700
This type of pore usually has red edges

00:04:01.700 --> 00:04:03.200
or

00:04:03.200 --> 00:04:05.500
a faint red bump at the bottom. Generally

00:04:05.500 --> 00:04:06.333
speaking,

00:04:06.333 --> 00:04:07.300
it will be parallel to

00:04:07.300 --> 00:04:10.000
or slightly raised on the surface of the skin. It

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:11.000
is mainly round holes,

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:12.400
usually not accompanied by oiliness

00:04:12.400 --> 00:04:14.133
, and nothing can be squeezed out.

00:04:14.233 --> 00:04:15.733
The appearance of this type of pore

00:04:15.733 --> 00:04:18.433
is actually caused by local inflammation.

00:04:18.433 --> 00:04:20.900
It will appear where you are sensitive.

00:04:20.900 --> 00:04:23.000
Therefore, when you are doing skin care,

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:25.533
you should also focus on anti-inflammatory actions.

00:04:25.533 --> 00:04:26.866
When your inflammation disappears,

00:04:26.866 --> 00:04:29.233
your pore problem will also be solved.

00:04:29.233 --> 00:04:30.866
So what specific products should

00:04:30.866 --> 00:04:32.033
I use? We will talk about

00:04:32.466 --> 00:04:34.800
the fifth type of carbonyl pores in detail later.

00:04:34.800 --> 00:04:35.400
Generally speaking,

00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:37.933
the color of carbonyl pores is consistent with the skin color.

00:04:37.933 --> 00:04:40.333
If the height is high, they will be sunken in the skin.

00:04:40.333 --> 00:04:43.866
The shape is usually teardrop-shaped or oval.

00:04:43.866 --> 00:04:46.433
They are usually not accompanied by oiliness and may even

00:04:46.433 --> 00:04:47.866
be dry and nothing can be squeezed out.

00:04:47.866 --> 00:04:50.400
This type of pores is also called aging pores.

00:04:50.400 --> 00:04:53.466
It is a part of the aging process of the whole face.

00:04:53.466 --> 00:04:54.800
The reason for its occurrence

00:04:54.800 --> 00:04:57.933
is that the collagen in your facial skin is lost.

00:04:57.933 --> 00:05:00.833
After the loss, not only can your skin not support

00:05:00.833 --> 00:05:02.866
your pores, but your pores can also not support

00:05:02.866 --> 00:05:05.400
your skin. Our pores in the skin

00:05:05.400 --> 00:05:08.100
are like a bag that can be lifted up.

00:05:08.100 --> 00:05:10.533
But if the collagen is lost,

00:05:10.533 --> 00:05:12.400
you can't lift this bag.

00:05:12.400 --> 00:05:15.233
It will just "pop" and fall on the table

00:05:15.233 --> 00:05:17.000
. You look very large

00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:18.133
and irregular.

00:05:18.133 --> 00:05:19.400
Your skin looks

00:05:19.400 --> 00:05:20.733
enlarged pores

00:05:20.733 --> 00:05:22.033
and Dull and

00:05:22.033 --> 00:05:23.266
rough -looking,

00:05:23.266 --> 00:05:24.466
aging-type pores

00:05:24.466 --> 00:05:25.933
actually happen to everyone

00:05:25.933 --> 00:05:27.700
as we age.

00:05:27.700 --> 00:05:29.133
But if we

00:05:29.133 --> 00:05:30.866
use anti-aging products in time

00:05:30.866 --> 00:05:32.866
, we can delay their occurrence

00:05:32.866 --> 00:05:35.533
or slow down their progression.

00:05:40.133 --> 00:05:42.233
After hearing about the types, you'll definitely be anxious.

00:05:42.233 --> 00:05:45.200
What if I have multiple types

00:05:45.200 --> 00:05:48.533
? Do I need

00:05:48.533 --> 00:05:49.433
to prioritize how to solve them?

00:05:49.433 --> 00:05:52.266
Different types actually have priorities.

00:05:52.266 --> 00:05:55.466
The first priority is urgent and important.

00:05:55.466 --> 00:05:56.433
This priority

00:05:56.433 --> 00:05:58.533
is inflammatory pores.

00:05:58.600 --> 00:06:00.833
As long as there is inflammation on your face,

00:06:00.833 --> 00:06:03.733
it will bring a series of various problems.

00:06:03.733 --> 00:06:04.900
If you don't solve it,

00:06:04.900 --> 00:06:07.266
it will continue to bring you new problems

00:06:07.266 --> 00:06:08.533
. The second priority

00:06:08.533 --> 00:06:11.500
is oily pores and keratinized pores.

00:06:11.500 --> 00:06:15.066
They are relatively easier to solve

00:06:15.066 --> 00:06:16.200
and can be solved locally.

00:06:16.200 --> 00:06:18.333
And the two pore types that

00:06:18.333 --> 00:06:19.600
show results relatively quickly.

00:06:19.933 --> 00:06:21.633
The third priority

00:06:21.633 --> 00:06:24.666
is the important but not urgent pore type

00:06:24.666 --> 00:06:27.666
, namely the glycated pores and carbonyl pores.

00:06:27.666 --> 00:06:31.066
Because both of them are problems of the whole face skin,

00:06:31.066 --> 00:06:32.400
not local problems

00:06:32.400 --> 00:06:35.433
, and require long-term care to be improved, then I will introduce

00:06:35.466 --> 00:06:38.133
the specific products and their corresponding solutions

00:06:38.133 --> 00:06:40.866
in order of priority. Let's talk

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:48.900
about the urgent and important inflammatory pores first.

00:06:48.900 --> 00:06:51.333
The main method for inflammatory pores

00:06:51.333 --> 00:06:55.800
is local or full-face soothing and anti-inflammatory treatment.

00:06:55.800 --> 00:06:57.200
When your inflammation disappears,

00:06:57.200 --> 00:06:59.000
your symptoms of pore discomfort

00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:00.833
and the appearance of the pores

00:07:00.833 --> 00:07:02.000
will be improved.

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:04.933
But when choosing products, you should pay attention to your skin type because

00:07:04.933 --> 00:07:06.400
the anti-inflammatory and soothing ingredients corresponding to

00:07:06.400 --> 00:07:08.500
dry skin and oily skin

00:07:08.500 --> 00:07:09.633
are different.

00:07:09.633 --> 00:07:12.333
For example, if you have oily or acne-prone skin,

00:07:12.333 --> 00:07:14.866
the most suitable anti-inflammatory and soothing ingredient for you

00:07:14.866 --> 00:07:16.133
is olive oil.

00:07:16.133 --> 00:07:18.433
Olive oil is added to an effective concentration

00:07:18.433 --> 00:07:21.500
and is more suitable for dealing with this type of pores.

00:07:21.500 --> 00:07:22.833
There are these products

00:07:22.833 --> 00:07:26.000
. If you have dry or combination skin,

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:27.800
you can choose

00:07:27.800 --> 00:07:28.866
soothing and anti-inflammatory products

00:07:28.866 --> 00:07:29.800
with ingredients such as

00:07:29.800 --> 00:07:30.400
B5 ceramide

00:07:30.400 --> 00:07:31.100
, urea

00:07:31.100 --> 00:07:33.100
, Centella asiatica

00:07:33.100 --> 00:07:34.666
, and Ectoin as

00:07:34.666 --> 00:07:35.600
the main ingredients . Because

00:07:35.600 --> 00:07:37.133
in addition to soothing and anti-inflammatory,

00:07:37.133 --> 00:07:39.533
they also have moisturizing and repairing functions.

00:07:39.600 --> 00:07:42.033
I have listed some products

00:07:42.033 --> 00:07:43.500
for your reference.

00:07:44.400 --> 00:07:47.266
Now let's talk about the two types of pores that are relatively quick

00:07:47.266 --> 00:07:48.633
and easy to solve:

00:07:48.633 --> 00:07:50.800
oily pores and keratinized pores.

00:07:51.000 --> 00:07:52.133
These two types of pores

00:07:52.133 --> 00:07:54.100
often appear on the face at the same time

00:07:54.100 --> 00:07:56.733
, and their solutions are also similar.

00:07:56.733 --> 00:07:59.300
The key word is cleaning.

00:07:59.400 --> 00:08:00.400
Why do I say that?

00:08:00.400 --> 00:08:01.633
Because you will find that both types

00:08:01.633 --> 00:08:04.800
can squeeze out dirt

00:08:04.800 --> 00:08:07.233
. If you squeeze out white and

00:08:07.233 --> 00:08:08.233
soft sebum, then

00:08:08.233 --> 00:08:09.666
you have oily pores,

00:08:09.666 --> 00:08:11.600
but if you squeeze out hard,

00:08:11.600 --> 00:08:14.000
dirty, gray keratin particles, then you have

00:08:14.000 --> 00:08:15.266
keratinized pores.

00:08:15.566 --> 00:08:16.866
The method of cleaning

00:08:16.866 --> 00:08:19.433
is to dissolve it first

00:08:19.433 --> 00:08:21.900
and then lift it out with external force.

00:08:21.900 --> 00:08:23.000
The commonly used method

00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:24.633
is to dissolve the blackheads. Sometimes

00:08:24.633 --> 00:08:26.600
blackhead water

00:08:26.600 --> 00:08:29.233
or acid or enzyme brushes are used

00:08:29.433 --> 00:08:31.400
. The methods to pick them out

00:08:31.400 --> 00:08:32.533
are either mud masks

00:08:32.533 --> 00:08:34.000
, nose strips

00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:36.433
, or cell clips.

00:08:36.566 --> 00:08:39.000
There are also some useful products

00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:40.800
for dissolving and pulling.

00:08:40.800 --> 00:08:43.700
For example, the products for blackhead water, acid and enzyme brushes

00:08:43.700 --> 00:08:44.700
are as follows, and

00:08:44.700 --> 00:08:47.900
the mud masks used for pulling are as follows.

00:08:48.066 --> 00:08:50.200
Then let's talk about

00:08:50.200 --> 00:08:53.433
the two types of pores that are the most difficult and take the longest time to deal with

00:08:53.433 --> 00:08:56.466
, namely glycated pores and glycated pores.

00:08:56.466 --> 00:08:58.400
The common point between the two

00:08:58.400 --> 00:09:01.633
is that it is not a local pore problem

00:09:01.633 --> 00:09:04.666
, but an aging problem for the entire face.

00:09:04.833 --> 00:09:07.500
Regardless of whether your skin has a high level of glycation

00:09:07.500 --> 00:09:09.800
or a more serious loss of collagen,

00:09:09.800 --> 00:09:12.100
it is a part of aging.

00:09:12.100 --> 00:09:13.866
Therefore, when we solve it,

00:09:13.866 --> 00:09:16.800
we do not use pore-type products,

00:09:16.800 --> 00:09:18.933
but anti-aging products.

00:09:18.933 --> 00:09:20.666
For example, for glycated pores,

00:09:20.666 --> 00:09:22.866
we need to use full-face anti-glycemic

00:09:22.866 --> 00:09:24.733
and antioxidant products,

00:09:24.733 --> 00:09:26.000
such as these

00:09:26.000 --> 00:09:27.866
. For carbonylation types,

00:09:27.866 --> 00:09:30.200
we need to use full-face products that promote collagen

00:09:30.200 --> 00:09:32.833
and reduce collagen loss.

00:09:33.200 --> 00:09:34.766
Now we understand

00:09:34.766 --> 00:09:36.566
the five types, how to judge

00:09:36.566 --> 00:09:38.533
them, and what can be used for them. Finally, let me talk about

00:09:38.533 --> 00:09:41.900
two very special pores.

00:09:41.900 --> 00:09:42.600
The first type

00:09:42.600 --> 00:09:44.700
is this pore. It looks very normal.

00:09:44.700 --> 00:09:47.466
It doesn't produce oil, redness, or blackness,

00:09:47.466 --> 00:09:50.900
but there is a small black dot in the center of the pore,

00:09:50.900 --> 00:09:53.000
and you can't squeeze this black dot out. In

00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:54.033
this case,

00:09:54.033 --> 00:09:57.733
I suggest you use a magnifying glass to carefully look at

00:09:57.733 --> 00:09:59.600
the black dot inside.

00:09:59.600 --> 00:10:01.933
Is it a hair?

00:10:01.933 --> 00:10:04.433
This young hair is called vellus hair

00:10:04.433 --> 00:10:06.733
, which is the hair in the baby stage.

00:10:06.733 --> 00:10:07.500
This hair

00:10:07.500 --> 00:10:09.933
may never grow out

00:10:09.933 --> 00:10:12.466
in its entire life. It is just at the bottom of the pore

00:10:12.466 --> 00:10:13.833
and stays there quietly.

00:10:13.833 --> 00:10:15.233
But you may feel

00:10:15.233 --> 00:10:18.700
that having a small black dot is particularly bad.

00:10:18.700 --> 00:10:21.466
Skin care products can't do anything about this,

00:10:21.466 --> 00:10:23.700
and you must never pull it out with tweezers.

00:10:23.700 --> 00:10:25.400
If you want to get rid of it,

00:10:25.400 --> 00:10:28.400
you can go to the hospital for laser hair removal

00:10:28.400 --> 00:10:29.466
to remove it.

00:10:29.466 --> 00:10:30.600
There is another

00:10:30.600 --> 00:10:33.466
type. There is a type of keratinized pore.

00:10:33.466 --> 00:10:35.066
You can clearly see a

00:10:35.066 --> 00:10:36.900
gray dirt in it,

00:10:36.900 --> 00:10:39.066
but you can't squeeze

00:10:39.200 --> 00:10:41.766
it out. It is actually a type of keratinized pore

00:10:41.766 --> 00:10:44.733
. This keratin plug has existed for too long and

00:10:44.733 --> 00:10:45.966
gradually oxidized

00:10:45.966 --> 00:10:48.800
and turned black, forming such a huge dirt.

00:10:48.800 --> 00:10:49.733
In this case

00:10:49.733 --> 00:10:52.333
, This keratin plug has been in

00:10:52.333 --> 00:10:54.133
your pores for a long time

00:10:54.133 --> 00:10:56.133
, and the dirt you see

00:10:56.133 --> 00:10:57.566
is just the tip of the iceberg.

00:10:57.566 --> 00:11:00.300
90% of it is under your skin,

00:11:00.300 --> 00:11:01.933
so you can't pull it out.

00:11:01.933 --> 00:11:03.433
When you are dealing with it,

00:11:03.433 --> 00:11:05.600
because we need a long time to dissolve it

00:11:05.600 --> 00:11:06.633
and promote metabolism,

00:11:06.633 --> 00:11:09.733
we try not to choose more irritating products

00:11:09.733 --> 00:11:11.866
, but choose mild enzymes

00:11:11.866 --> 00:11:14.000
to dissolve it little by little, and then

00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:16.266
let it metabolize the product layer by layer

00:11:16.266 --> 00:11:18.466
in the process of promoting keratin metabolism

00:11:18.466 --> 00:11:19.600
. You can refer to

00:11:19.600 --> 00:11:22.933
products such as enzyme brushes

00:11:22.933 --> 00:11:25.633
used in keratin-type pores

00:11:25.633 --> 00:11:27.100
, and then use them for a long time.

00:11:27.366 --> 00:11:28.200
That's all for

